TOPIC: TERRAFORM INTRODUCTION, CREATING AN EC2 INSTANCE USING TERRAFORM
================================================================================

TERRAFORM -----------> Means IAAC(Infrastructure As A Code) -------> we can create different ways to create the Infrastructure------------> we can create as Manual way,
through CLI(Command Line Interface) & Automation


there is a reusability is present 

Alternatives for IAAC is Terraform, ARM(Azure templates) for using AZURE, CFT (Cloud Formaton Template) for using AWS, GRM for using GCP

Terraform supports multi cloud

To learn Terraform we need to learn Hashicorp language, by using this Hashicorp language with terraform we can create infrastructure in any kind of cloud

Now we will do in practical way

By using Terraform we can create EC2, SE, VPC, IAM, Autoscaling groups, LoadBalancers

First launch one ec2-instance ---------> name: terraform ---------> with keypair-----------> c7i-flex.large------> security groups--------> 28ebs volume------------>
launch and connect ec2-instance

Now we need to install Terraform in it

go to this website -------> https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/install--------> select Linux ---------> select Amazon Linux------>copy all commands and paste here 

go to this website to install locally on laptop ----------------------> https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/tutorials/aws-get-started/install-cli

